  "body": "# Feature Issue\n\nThe payment request screen should show the amount with decimals and the symbol of the ERC20 token used for the payment.\n\nThe current implementation shows the amount without decimals (in the screenshot below it shows 1 and 18 zeros instead of 1), and the token address (instead of showing STT, the SNT test token deployed on Ropsten).\n\n![01](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1059/77440564-c0a37700-6de8-11ea-934e-fb1217dbeb4c.jpg)\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\nGiven any token address, the request screen should show  the right amount and symbol based on the values returned after calling the `decimal` and `symbol` methods of the ERC20 contract.\n\n### Notes\n\nThe request screen is implemented in the `feature/9275-keycard-signTypedData` branch.\n\nTest app at https://status-im.github.io/keycard-cash-test-dapp/. It's a simple dapp we can use from the Status browser to test this feature.",
